13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 698.4 of Title 70, unless there
16 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 A. As used in this section, “eligible school district” means a
18 public school district or public school district foundation in this
19 state that has established a program to provide tuition or loan
20 repayment assistance to school district employees who pursue an
21 undergraduate degree from a teacher preparation program accredited
22 by the Commission for Educational Quality and Accountability leading
23 to a standard teaching certificate.
24
SB235 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 B. There is hereby created the Grow Your Own Educator Program
2 to provide matching fund grants to eligible school districts. The
3 program shall be established and maintained by the Office of
4 Educational Quality and Accountability.
5 C. An eligible school district seeking to participate in the
6 Grow Your Own Educator Program shall submit an application in the
7 manner and on a form prescribed by the Office of Educational Quality
8 and Accountability. The application shall include:
9 1. The amount of matching fund grants requested;
10 2. The position of the employee pursuing an undergraduate
11 degree from a teacher preparation program; and
12 3. The subject area in which the employee is pursuing an
13 undergraduate degree from a teacher preparation program.
14 D. Matching fund grants shall be awarded on a first-come,
15 first-served basis. Grants shall be provided without any limitation
16 other than the amount of funds available in the Grow Your Own
17 Educator Revolving Fund created pursuant to Section 2 of this act
18 and the number of eligible school districts that apply.
19 E. By June 30, 2026, and each June 30 thereafter, an eligible
20 school district that receives a matching fund grant pursuant to this
21 section shall electronically submit a report to the Office of
22 Educational Quality and Accountability that includes:
